==English==

===Etymology===
Compound of ''[[sun]]'' + ''[[rise]]''

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|En-ca-sunrise.ogg|Audio (CA)}}

===Adjective===
'''sunrise'''

# Pertaining to an unusually early time of day.
#:''The '''sunrise'''-service will be at 6:30AM.''

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# {{time}}: The [[time]] of [[day]] when the [[sun]] [[appear]]s above the [[eastern]] [[horizon]].
#:''I'll meet you at the docks at '''sunrise'''.''
# The [[change]] in [[color]] of the [[sky]] at sunrise.
#:''Did you see the beautiful '''sunrise''' this morning?''
# ''(figurative):'' Any great awakening.
#:''It was the '''sunrise''' of her spirit.''

====Synonyms====
*[[sunup]] (1)
*[[crack of dawn]]
*[[dawn]]

